exports[`docs CLI > docs dump --format markdown 1`] = `
"# akg-ts Documentation


## api_symbol

**CascadeDeleteResult** (\`api_symbol/CascadeDeleteResult\`)
> Result of deleteNodeCascade: counts of deleted inbound edges, outbound edges, and node.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`

**Edge** (\`api_symbol/Edge\`)
> An edge record returned by read operations; includes from, relation, to, strength, confidence, meta, and timestamps.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`

**EdgeFields** (\`api_symbol/EdgeFields\`)
> Input fields for putEdge: strength (default 0.5), confidence (default null), meta (optional).
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`

**EdgeFilter** (\`api_symbol/EdgeFilter\`)
> Filter criteria for listEdges: relation and meta.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`

**InvalidInputError** (\`api_symbol/InvalidInputError\`)
> Thrown when a caller passes an argument that violates a format or semantic constraint.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`

**MissingRequiredFieldError** (\`api_symbol/MissingRequiredFieldError\`)
> Thrown when a required field is absent, such as omitting title in putNode.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`

**Node** (\`api_symbol/Node\`)
> A node record returned by read operations; includes id, type, title, body, meta, tags, and SDK-managed timestamps.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`

**NodeFields** (\`api_symbol/NodeFields\`)
> Input fields for putNode: title (required), body (optional), meta (optional).
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`

**NodeFilter** (\`api_symbol/NodeFilter\`)
> Filter criteria for listNodesFiltered: type, tag, and meta with AND semantics.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`

**NodeRef** (\`api_symbol/NodeRef\`)
> Identifies a node by type and id; returned by putNode and accepted by edge and query methods.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`

**NotFoundError** (\`api_symbol/NotFoundError\`)
> Thrown when a deleteNode or deleteEdge target does not exist.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`

**ReconcileResult** (\`api_symbol/ReconcileResult\`)
> Result of reconcileOutboundEdges: counts of added, removed, and unchanged edges.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`

**Snapshot** (\`api_symbol/Snapshot\`)
> JSON-serializable record of all live nodes and edges returned by store.snapshot().
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`

**Store** (\`api_symbol/Store\`)
> The main class for reading and writing an AKG knowledge graph.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`

**close** (\`api_symbol/close\`)
> Commits outstanding mutations and closes the store; safe to call with no pending mutations.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`, \`lifecycle\`

**commit** (\`api_symbol/commit\`)
> Durably writes all pending in-memory mutations to the .akg file.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`, \`lifecycle\`

**compact** (\`api_symbol/compact\`)
> Rewrites the .akg file with only live records, discarding WAL history and tombstones.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`, \`lifecycle\`

**deleteEdge** (\`api_symbol/deleteEdge\`)
> Deletes an edge; throws NotFoundError if the edge does not exist.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`

**deleteNode** (\`api_symbol/deleteNode\`)
> Deletes a node; throws NotFoundError if missing, InvalidInputError if live edges remain.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`

**deleteNodeCascade** (\`api_symbol/deleteNodeCascade\`)
> Deletes all inbound and outbound edges then deletes the node; returns a CascadeDeleteResult.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`

**getNode** (\`api_symbol/getNode\`)
> Returns the node at (typeName, id), or null if it does not exist.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`

**getNodes** (\`api_symbol/getNodes\`)
> Batch-fetches nodes by NodeRef array; returns null at positions where a node does not exist.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`

**inboundEdges** (\`api_symbol/inboundEdges\`)
> Returns all inbound edges to a node, optionally filtered by relation.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`

**listEdges** (\`api_symbol/listEdges\`)
> Returns all edges, optionally filtered by relation or metadata.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`

**listNodes** (\`api_symbol/listNodes\`)
> Returns all nodes, optionally filtered to a given type name, sorted by key.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`

**listNodesByTag** (\`api_symbol/listNodesByTag\`)
> Returns all nodes carrying the given tag, sorted by key.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`

**listNodesFiltered** (\`api_symbol/listNodesFiltered\`)
> Returns nodes matching a NodeFilter combining type, tag, and metadata criteria.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`

**open** (\`api_symbol/open\`)
> Opens an existing .akg file or creates a new empty one; returns a Store.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`, \`lifecycle\`

**outboundEdges** (\`api_symbol/outboundEdges\`)
> Returns all outbound edges from a node, optionally filtered by relation.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`

**putEdge** (\`api_symbol/putEdge\`)
> Writes or replaces an edge between two existing nodes.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`

**putNode** (\`api_symbol/putNode\`)
> Writes or replaces a node at (typeName, id); returns a NodeRef.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`

**recentEdges** (\`api_symbol/recentEdges\`)
> Returns edges sorted newest-first by updatedAt, with optional source, relation, and limit filters.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`

**recentNodes** (\`api_symbol/recentNodes\`)
> Returns nodes sorted newest-first by updatedAt, with optional type, tag, and limit filters.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`

**reconcileOutboundEdges** (\`api_symbol/reconcileOutboundEdges\`)
> Synchronizes the outbound edges for a source node and relation to exactly the desired target set.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`

**snapshot** (\`api_symbol/snapshot\`)
> Returns a JSON-serializable Snapshot of all live nodes and edges in deterministic order.
Tags: \`api\`, \`typescript\`


## concept

**Compaction** (\`concept/compaction\`)
> Rewrites the file to contain only live records, discarding WAL history; caller-triggered, never automatic.
Tags: \`concept\`, \`lifecycle\`, \`typescript\`, \`normative\`

**Naming rules** (\`concept/naming_rules\`)
> Type names, relation names, and tags must be lowercase [a-z0-9_] with no leading, trailing, or consecutive underscores.
Tags: \`concept\`, \`normative\`, \`typescript\`

**Single-writer semantics** (\`concept/single_writer\`)
> Only one process should have a store open for writing at a time; concurrent access produces undefined behavior.
Tags: \`concept\`, \`normative\`, \`typescript\`

**Write-Ahead Log (WAL)** (\`concept/wal\`)
> Mutations are held in memory and appended to a WAL on commit; not visible to other processes until committed.
Tags: \`concept\`, \`lifecycle\`, \`typescript\`, \`normative\`


## warning

**Delete edges before nodes** (\`warning/delete_edges_before_nodes\`)
> You must delete all inbound and outbound edges before deleting a node; the graph does not cascade-delete automatically.
Tags: \`warning\`, \`typescript\`, \`normative\`

**Uncommitted mutations are lost** (\`warning/uncommitted_mutations\`)
> Mutations held in memory are lost if the process exits without calling commit or close.
Tags: \`warning\`, \`typescript\`, \`lifecycle\`

"
`;

